Diagnnosis: Recognized by the brown coloration, the small size, total length 2.12–2.40 , elongate ovoid to ovate, and the form of the male genitalia. Antennal segment I black, segment II yellowish distally, or entirely black, segment III and segment IV ranging from almost yellowish to entirely black. Femora black with narrow, yellow distal bands (
Fig. 16
).

Male genitalia (
Figs. 24–26
): Vesica tapering towards apex; secondary gonopore well sclerotized, distant from apex of vesica.
